, at the University of René Descartes in Paris, (where she obtained PhD in Public Law) and at the University of Iceland ( LLM in Natural Resources Law and International Environmental Law).In 2011, she was appointed by the University of Laval (Canada, Quebec) as a researcher and a lecturer in Environmental Law.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aThis eBook is made available Open Access. Unless otherwise specified individually in the content, the work is licensed under the Creative Commons Attribution-NonCommercial-NoDerivatives (CC BY-NC-ND) license: uhttps://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-nd/3.0 uhttps://www.degruyter.com/dg/page/open-access-policy  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 02. Feb 2021) 0aDemocracyxEnvironmental aspects. 0aEnvironmental policyxCitizen participation. 0aEnvironmentalism. 7aLAW / Civil Law.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertE-BOOK GESAMTPAKET / COMPLETE PACKAGE 2013z9783110317350oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertE-BOOK PACKAGE HISTORY, POLITICAL SCIENCE, SOCIOLOGY 2013z978311031712108iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertE-BOOK PAKET GESCHICHTE, POLITIKWISS., SOZIOLOGIE 2013z9783110317114oZDB-23-DPS0 cprintz978837656013740uhttps://doi.org/10.2478/9788376560144zOpen Access7040uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9788376560144zOpen Access70423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9788376560144.jpg  a978-3-11-031712-1 E-BOOK PACKAGE HISTORY, POLITICAL SCIENCE, SOCIOLOGY 2013b2013  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aZDB-23-DGGb2013  aZDB-23-DPSb2013  aZDB-23-GOA